  "text": "Three weeks after implantation of the canullae the ewes were divided into two groups and infused ICV with a vehicle (control, n=5), or genistein, 10 μg/ 100 μl/h (total 40 μg, n=5). The dose of genistein was selected according to our previous study [CITATION_1] , in which it elicited significant changes in the secretion of the studied hormones in ewes kept under increasing day length conditions. All infusions were performed from 12.00 to 16.00 h and blood samples were collected from 8.00 to 20.00 h, at 10-min intervals through a catheter inserted into the jugular vein a day before the experiment. After centrifugation in heparinized tubes, plasma was stored at -20°C until hormone assays were performed.",
